# Mobile App Standards

Native mobile app development standards (Post-MVP).

## Technology Stack

- **iOS:** Swift (iOS 17+)
- **Android:** Kotlin (Android 12+)
- **Lightweight clients** - Minimal business logic

## Architecture

- **Offline-first** with local storage
- **Sync engine** with last-write-wins resolution
- **Background sync** for data updates
- **Biometric authentication** (Face ID / Touch ID)

## Storage

- **iOS:** Core Data or SwiftData
- **Android:** Room database
- **Token storage:** Keychain (iOS), EncryptedSharedPreferences (Android)

## Requirements

- **Keep mobile apps lightweight** - Business logic in backend
- **API communication only** - No complex calculations
- **Offline support** with sync when online

## Examples

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - Lightweight API client
func fetchTasks(weekId: String) async throws -> [Task] {
    return try await apiClient.get("/api/v1/weeks/\(weekId)/tasks")
}
```

```kotlin
